# APIs and integration — [[project_name]]

## lib/apis/ structure

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apis/common/constants.dart` | `apiUrl`, headers |
| `apis/common/data_source_config.dart` | Per-entity mock vs remote registry |
| `apis/interceptors/` | Dio interceptors (auth, logging) |
| `apis/core/` | Dio injectable module |

**Mock data:** `assets/mock/<entity>.json` — see `docs/architecture/MOCK_AND_REMOTE_DATA.md`.

## Mock vs remote

Each domain entity has `I*Service` with **mock** (JSON assets) and **remote** (Retrofit) implementations. `DataSourceConfig.entities` selects which implementation DI provides. Default: **mock**.

Read `docs/architecture/MOCK_AND_REMOTE_DATA.md` before adding entities or switching to remote.

## When to add API code

Add or extend `<entity>_remote_service.dart` when an epic needs HTTP endpoints. DTOs live in `lib/domain/<entity>/infrastructure/<entity>_dto.dart`. Repositories inject `I<Entity>Service`, never Retrofit directly.

## Integration wiring (subagent: integration-wiring)

After domain and feature layers exist:

1. **router.dart** — import new page, add `GoRoute` with path and name consistent with existing routes.
2. **injection.dart** — ensure `configureDependencies()` covers new `@injectable` classes and service modules.
3. **data_source_config.dart** — register new entity as `DataSource.mock` (or `remote` when API ready).
4. **assets/mock/** — create/update `<entity>.json` with sample data.
5. **error_localizer.dart** — add `localize<Entity>Failure` method per new `*_failure.dart`.
6. **build_runner** — run after Injectable/Freezed/Retrofit changes:
   ```
   dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
   ```

## Rules

- No UI in `lib/apis/`.
- Presentation never calls Retrofit directly — use repository from domain.
- Remote entities require non-empty `Constants.apiUrl` (validated at startup).
